<section class="min-vh-50 bg-white alignment">
  <div class="container py-5">
    <div class="row py-5">
      <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6 pb-3">
        <h2 class="sub">“Almost 3 million new gardening projects in the last year, nearly half of new gardeners under 45”</h2>
        <p class="pt-3 a">
          <%= link_to "hortweek", "https://www.hortweek.com/new-gardener-estimates-treble-month/retail/article/1693981", target: :_blank %>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
          <p>Research showed a huge boost in gardening during the Corona pandemic, especially amongst under 45s. The <%= link_to "HTA Garden Retail Monitor", "https://hta.org.uk/", target: :_blank %> found that sales of gardening products were up 34%, 17% and 19% in June, July and August respectively in UK garden centres in 2020, compared to 2019. On average, individual customers were spending 35% more on gardening products.</p>
          <p>The eco plusses of gardening are also considerable—from supporting beneficial insects and birds, to reducing the carbon footprint of home-grown food, to increasing oxygen in the air.</p>
          <p>And what about eco-gardening?</p>
          <%= link_to "67% of UK gardeners", "https://www.hortweek.com/covid-19-transformed-gardening-industry-%E2%80%93-so-new-trends/retail/article/1701037", target: :_blank, class: "" %> say they’re eco-conscious and 46% of this group already use organic fertilisers. 
          <%= link_to "The 2021 Organic Market Report", "https://www.soilassociation.org/certification/market-research-and-data/the-organic-market-report-2021/", target: :_blank, class: "" %> revealed the highest year-on-year growth in 15 years for the organic market, at +12.6%, with the market now worth £2.79B.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="min-vh-50 bg-white alignment">
  <div class="container py-5">
