      <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6 pb-3">
        <h2 class="sub">“Almost 3 million new gardening projects in the last year, nearly half of new gardeners under 45”</h2>
        <p class="quote pt-3">Dr Alan Kellas, Royal College of Psychiatrists, 
          <%= link_to "theguardian.com", "https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/may/17/how-lockdown-has-created-veg-growing-revolution-uk-coronavirus", target: :_blank %>
        </p>
      </div>
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
          <p>The mental health benefits of gardening have been widely documented. A huge study by the <%= link_to "University of Exeter", "https://www.exeter.ac.uk/news/research/title_793983_en.html", target: :_blank %> on gardens and gardening showed that people who spent time in the garden report better physical and mental health levels than those who do not.</p>
          <p>The eco plusses of gardening are also considerable—from supporting beneficial insects and birds, to reducing the carbon footprint of home-grown food, to increasing oxygen in the air.</p>
          <p>As a team we decided on what was feasible to build in the timeframe and focused on growing vegetables so there would be a delicious reward at the end of each growing cycle.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>






